import React, { useState } from 'react' import TopNav from '../components/TopNav' import { Container, Row, Col, Card, Form, Button } from 'react-bootstrap' import { predictSingle } from '../services/api' import { toast } from 'react-toastify' export default function PredictSingle() { // FULL STUDENT PAYLOAD (same fields your ML API expects) const [form, setForm] = useState({ passed_out_10: 2022, passed_out_11: 2023, passed_out_12: 2024, marks_10: 80, marks_11: 80, marks_12: 80, family_income: 20000, family_members: 4, academic_score: 75, motivation_level: 3, attendance_rate: 80, district: "Chennai", school_type_10: "Government", school_type_11: "Government", school_type_12: "Government", orphan: "No", single_parent: "No", girl_child: "No", communication_frequency: "Medium", family_support: "Medium", extra_curricular: "No", interest_level: "Medium", attitude: "Respectful", school_fee_6_to_12: "10k-20k" }); const [result, setResult] = useState(null); const updateField = (key, val) => { setForm(prev => ({ ...prev, [key]: val })); } const submit = async (e) => { e.preventDefault(); // ðŸ”¥ FULL PAYLOAD REQUIRED BY FLASK MODEL const payload = { name: "Test Student", district: form.district || "Chennai", passed_out_10: form.passed_out_10 || 2022, passed_out_11: form.passed_out_11 || 2023, passed_out_12: form.passed_out_12 || 2024, marks_10: form.marks_10 || 80, marks_11: form.marks_11 || 80, marks_12: form.marks_12 || 80, school_name_10: "", school_name_11: "", school_name_12: "", school_type_10: form.school_type_10 || "Government", school_type_11: form.school_type_11 || "Government", school_type_12: form.school_type_12 || "Government", family_income: form.family_income || 20000, family_members: form.family_members || 4, orphan: form.orphan || "No", single_parent: form.single_parent || "No", girl_child: form.girl_child || "No", siblings: form.siblings || "No", siblings_details: "", siblings_work_or_college: "", rent_or_own: "Rent", property_owned: "No", parents_occupation: "Labour", private_or_govt_school: "Government", willing_hostel: "Yes", any_scholarship: "No", first_graduate: "Yes", scholarship_eligibility: "Yes", academic_score: form.academic_score, motivation_level: form.motivation_level, attendance_rate: form.attendance_rate, communication_frequency: form.communication_frequency || "Medium", family_support: form.family_support || "Medium", extra_curricular: form.extra_curricular || "No", interest_level: form.interest_level || "Medium", attitude: form.attitude || "Respectful", home_address: "", school_fee_6_to_12: form.school_fee_6_to_12 || "10k-20k" }; try { const res = await predictSingle(payload); setResult(res); toast.success("Prediction successful!"); } catch (err) { toast.error("Prediction failed"); } }; return ( <>
